# 16. UI Theming Requirements

## 16.1 Dark Mode is Mandatory

Every UI component built for this SPA must support both light and dark themes.

This is enforced via NativeWind's `dark:` class variants:

```tsx
// Required pattern
<View className="bg-white dark:bg-gray-900">
  <Text className="text-gray-900 dark:text-white">Content</Text>
</View>
```

Theme state is managed by `ThemeProvider` (see `src/shared/contexts/ThemeContext.tsx`).
Components do not read the theme directly — they rely on NativeWind resolving `dark:` classes automatically.

## 16.2 Theme Testing Requirement

Any component with theme-sensitive styling must have a corresponding Playwright E2E test that:

1. Verifies the component renders correctly in the default theme
2. Clicks the theme toggle button (`data-testid="theme-toggle"`) and verifies no errors occur
3. Confirms the component remains functional after a theme switch

Reference: `e2e/theme-toggle.spec.ts`

A component without theme coverage is considered **incomplete** and must not be merged.

